<title>POLAND: ZABRZE FINALISES GM DEAL.</title>
<headline>ZABRZE FINALISES GM DEAL.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Polish construction company Mostostal-Zabrze has signed an 87.6-million-mark contract to build a plant for Germany's Adam Opel AG, a General Motors Corp unit, Mostostal said in a statement on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Last week Mostostal had said Opel would award it a 90 million mark contract to build the Opel plant.</p>
<p>The contract encompasses the construction of the main buildings of the 500 million mark car factory, located in the southern town of Gliwice, to be completed in 1998's first half.</p>
<p>The car plant is to employ 2,000 and assemble 72,000 vehicles annually.</p>
<p>Last year, Mostostal Zabrze signed a 17 million mark contract with Adam Opel for other construction project at the site. -- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
